cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with information-theoretic secrecy in a network setting, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of a secret key to infuse privacy into the encoding suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The fact that the network involves communication between nodes suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of payoff functions and optimization suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
